org.gradoop.temporal.model.impl.operators.keyedgrouping.keys

Class DurationKeyFunction<T extends TemporalElement>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gradoop.temporal.model.impl.operators.keyedgrouping.keys.DurationKeyFunction<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the temporal elements.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, KeyFunction<T,Long>

    public class DurationKeyFunction<T extends TemporalElement>
extends Object
implements KeyFunction<T,Long>
    A key function extracting the duration of a temporal attribute.

    This key function extracts a time interval from an element and calculates the duration of that element in a certain TemporalUnit (e.g. seconds). Calculations will assume the time zone to be UTC.

    The final grouping key will be stored on the super element as a property with key duration_INTERVAL_UNIT where INTERVAL is the TimeDimension extracted and UNIT the TemporalUnit to be calculated.

        Store a key on an element.

        This is used to store the grouping key on the super element after grouping.

        The default implementation of this function does not change the element.

        Specified by:

        Parameters:
        element - The element where the key should be stored.
        key - The key to store on the element. The type of the key is expected to be the same as the type of keys extracted by this key function.
